Since all of our go-to pizza spots either don't deliver or closed due to the pandemic, we've been looking for new places to scratch that itch. Two Boots has made a compelling argument for becoming our new favorite pizzeria. The quality of the ingredients and preparation are as good as I've had in nearly a decade of living in Brooklyn. The meats are savory and crispy, the cheeses are flavorful and moist. The dough smells great and the crust is both crisp on the outside and chewy on the inside. The variety of pies on the menu is impressive, and even the less conventional ones sound delicious, given the quality I'd expect. Best of all, the price is totally reasonable for the amount of pizza you get (18" LG / 16" MD). Give them a try.
